  "text": "Subjects were 14 wild-caught New Caledonian crows held in captivity for 10 to 17 weeks before testing began (table 1). All birds had previously taken part in experiments involving tooluse and learning object properties, and some had taken part in a cooperative study with conspecifics (light blue, D3R, D4R, D4B and RWY [CITATION_1] ), but no subjects had ever been required to attend to human actions or the movement of rewards.",
